{
  "texts": [
    "The current version of Wordflow requires users to copy and paste their input text into a webpage or Google Doc.",
    "To minimize disruption to users' workflow (e.g., drafting an email, replying messages, or editing a PowerPoint), future researchers can make Wordflow in situ and ubiquitous.",
    "For example, Wordflow can be directly integrated into an operating system, running a prompt when users select text and trigger a keyboard shortcut.",
    "Wordflow supports both external LLM API services and on-device LLMs for running users' prompts ( § 3.4).",
    "With recent advancements in machine learning compilation [15] and model compression [28], we see great potential for on-device LLMs."
  ]
}